column5: ...what day would you pick for a cruise around Georgian Bay for Muskie and why?
I was waitin for Lew or Dan to chime in and say "let me check my calender" Don ! LOL  I've got too much to accomplish this week...but I'm getting that "need" again already !

Theres guys here that know a heck of alot more about musky than me here. But during the summer, if theres been a few days of stable weather, I'd want to be on the water the day the weather breaks. Try and be on a spot maybe I'd raised a fish recently, but not been able to convert. Sometimes the weather change gets the big girls going.
You know me too well Wayne .....  I checked my calander........and now you have an email
I'd be fishing in the rain.

Looks like it's gonna be the day after two days of rain! LOL  ..and I just looked at the weather and now it looks like that day, wed, instead of sunny is now WET FLURRIES! Just might be using the top Lew!
Nuthin wrong with fishing in the snow Wayne, at least we won't be bothered by skeeters
Nothing wrong with fishing in the snow.. only thing that would worry me is pulling the boat out of the water on the icey/snowy/slippery ramp..

Well wayne get that top & cover on and set a nice heater inside,and you and lew are ready to go !!!!!!   so what day are you heading out to georgian bay wednesday??....i might do a day trip to quinte this week,or shore fish as my back is feeling better....i need to go bad,  julie is getting feed-up with me whinning that i havnt gone fishing in almost 2 weeks....
